WEBVTT

00:07.424 --> 00:10.507
RUSSELL:
Ah, fucking silver.

00:12.346 --> 00:14.257
Your father deserved it, you know.

00:14.431 --> 00:16.046
Just as you deserve this.

00:16.225 --> 00:19.262
All I wanted was a couple of goats
for my wolves.

00:19.436 --> 00:23.429
You slaughtered my entire family
for a couple of goats.

00:23.607 --> 00:24.596
[CHUCKLES]

00:25.901 --> 00:27.857
GODRIC [IN SWEDISH]:
Forgive him, Eric.

00:29.279 --> 00:30.564
RUSSELL:
Goats.

00:30.739 --> 00:31.945
End all this hate...

00:32.115 --> 00:33.321
[RUSSELL SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

00:33.492 --> 00:35.574
...while you still can.

00:35.744 --> 00:37.359
Forgiveness is love.

00:38.664 --> 00:40.279
Love is all.

00:40.624 --> 00:42.455
No.

00:43.377 --> 00:46.210
RUSSELL:
Just shut the fuck up and die, please.

00:46.380 --> 00:48.086
I swore to my father.

00:48.257 --> 00:50.964
Your father was a self-important,
greedy little putz...

00:51.134 --> 00:52.874
...and he got what was coming to him.

00:53.637 --> 00:55.218
Only peace...

00:55.389 --> 00:56.970
...follows death...

00:57.140 --> 00:58.641
...for all.

00:58.809 --> 01:00.049
Even for him.

01:00.936 --> 01:03.268
[YELLING]

01:26.461 --> 01:27.746
SooMe.

01:30.173 --> 01:32.835
You fucking betrayed me again.

01:33.010 --> 01:37.049
| only pretended to betray you
so that I could save your life again.

01:37.222 --> 01:38.678
And it worked. Russell is gone.

01:40.392 --> 01:41.552
Where's Eric?

01:41.727 --> 01:44.434
Outside, burning.

01:44.605 --> 01:45.640
SOOKIE:
What?

01:45.814 --> 01:49.022
He bound himself by silver to the king.
Was the only way to kill him.

01:49.192 --> 01:50.648
I can't let him do that.

01:52.195 --> 01:53.810
BILL:
SooMe.

01:53.989 --> 01:57.197
You do not own me.

02:03.040 --> 02:04.621
Eric, this is just stupid.

02:04.791 --> 02:07.203
Go away.

02:07.377 --> 02:09.083
[IN SWEDISH]
Eric. Forgive him.

02:09.254 --> 02:10.630
In the brief time you have left.

02:10.797 --> 02:12.207
No forgiveness.

02:12.382 --> 02:14.373
I won't let you do this.

02:15.260 --> 02:17.251
Sweetie, please. Use your gift.

02:17.429 --> 02:19.215
-I don't know how.
-Yes, you do.

02:19.389 --> 02:22.096
Don't think about it. Don't try.

02:22.267 --> 02:25.054
I will not surrender to the true death.

02:25.228 --> 02:27.139
I will find a way to come back...

02:27.314 --> 02:30.727
...and kill your precious Viking
and your brooding Mr. Compton...

02:30.901 --> 02:34.064
...and his unbearable progeny
and anyone you ever cared about...

02:34.237 --> 02:38.150
...and all because you didn't use
your fucking power!

02:38.325 --> 02:39.565
[SOOKIE YELLS]

02:39.743 --> 02:41.699
[RUSSELL LAUGHING]

02:41.870 --> 02:44.407
Well, it's about fucking time.

02:44.581 --> 02:47.243
Now drag me the fuck inside.

02:50.962 --> 02:53.544
[LAUGHING]

02:53.715 --> 02:56.331
You watch your fucking language.

04:34.274 --> 04:36.856
PAM:
He needs blood. Human blood.

04:37.027 --> 04:38.688
He's too weak to drop fang.

04:39.529 --> 04:40.689
Bite me.

04:41.531 --> 04:43.032
PAM:
Thank God, the key.

05:03.595 --> 05:04.960
Keep an eye on him.

05:05.138 --> 05:06.924
We both know he could lose control.

05:15.357 --> 05:19.100
This is all part of a concerted effort
on the part of the right-wing fringe...

05:19.277 --> 05:20.938
...to stir up fear of vampires.

05:21.112 --> 05:24.900
Oh, was it the right wing that ripped
a guy's spine out on live television?

05:25.075 --> 05:30.741
No, but it is the right wing saying that all
vampires need to be wiped out of existence.

05:30.914 --> 05:33.496
Following that logic,
Osama bin Laden is human...

05:33.667 --> 05:36.750
...therefore all humans need to be
wiped out of existence.

05:36.920 --> 05:40.754
Did you hear that? All human beings
must be wiped out of existence.

05:40.924 --> 05:44.007
The vampire agenda,
pure and simple.

05:48.932 --> 05:50.297
I didn't know you could cook.

05:50.684 --> 05:52.174
I never made breakfast for you?

05:52.853 --> 05:54.263
Huh.

05:54.437 --> 05:59.272
Maybe that's because you always snuck out
before I woke up.

05:59.442 --> 06:04.277
Maybe that's because you always
woke me up, barking in your sleep.

06:07.284 --> 06:09.946
There's a reason for that.

06:12.122 --> 06:13.828
Hoecakes?

06:14.291 --> 06:20.161
My adopted mother, in addition to being
a repressed, codependent doormat...

06:20.338 --> 06:22.795
...was kind of a great Southern cook.

06:23.592 --> 06:26.459
-Bacon grease.
-It's all about the bacon grease.

06:30.390 --> 06:32.722
There's a reason why I bark in my sleep.

06:35.812 --> 06:37.848
Do not tell me you're a fucking werewolf.

06:38.023 --> 06:39.684
No.No,no.

06:39.858 --> 06:42.975
Because there are already too many
supernatural freaks in my life...

06:43.153 --> 06:45.235
-...as it is.
-Tara, I'm not a werewolf.

06:47.198 --> 06:49.814
Thank you, God, for once.

06:50.493 --> 06:51.903
I'm a shape-shifter.

06:52.329 --> 06:54.615
You're a shape-sh--?

06:56.583 --> 06:58.039
Shut the fuck up.

06:58.209 --> 07:02.578
No, I'm not gonna shut the fuck up about it,
Tara. It's what I am.

07:03.173 --> 07:04.663
It's who I am.

07:09.930 --> 07:11.545
That's enough.

07:20.190 --> 07:22.522
ERIC: Where's Russell?
-Outside.

07:22.692 --> 07:25.274
-We have to bring him in.
-Are you insane? Why?

07:25.737 --> 07:28.854
Godric appeared to me
and asked me to spare Russell.

07:29.866 --> 07:31.652
-You are insane.
-Sookie--

07:31.826 --> 07:36.786
You want me to go get the guy who wants
to kill us all and bring him inside? Really?

07:36.957 --> 07:39.573
Eric, do the world a favor
and let that little fuck fry.

07:42.087 --> 07:43.247
I'll go out there myself.

07:48.259 --> 07:50.511
Oh, for the love of God.

07:59.396 --> 08:00.806
I'm here to save you.

08:00.981 --> 08:03.597
RUSSELL:
Ah. Thank you, Miss Stackhouse.

08:03.775 --> 08:04.810
Shutup.

08:04.985 --> 08:08.273
[RUSSELL GROANING]

08:16.663 --> 08:20.247
Don't you think being a shape-shifter is
something you should tell a person...

08:20.417 --> 08:22.783
...before you sleep with them?

08:22.961 --> 08:25.202
Maybe. If it is, I apologize.

08:25.380 --> 08:27.746
I cannot deal with nonhumans right now.

08:27.924 --> 08:31.166
Tara, Franklin was a psychopath.

08:31.344 --> 08:33.300
I know you're not a psycho, Sam.

08:33.471 --> 08:37.259
But too many bad things have happened
to me because of supernatural stuff.

08:37.434 --> 08:38.640
And humans.

08:38.810 --> 08:40.675
God.

08:41.771 --> 08:44.183
Wish I could just reboot.

08:46.943 --> 08:49.525
Be a completely new person.

08:51.156 --> 08:53.147
In a brand-new life.

08:54.034 --> 08:58.448
Without knowing any of the shit
I have learned recently.

08:59.247 --> 09:00.612
You can.

09:01.291 --> 09:04.158
Be surprised how easy it is,
someone smart as you.

09:04.335 --> 09:09.625
And the other you, the old you,
never catches up?

09:11.009 --> 09:13.500
Well, of course it does.

09:13.678 --> 09:15.839
That's why you just gotta
keep on moving.

09:20.977 --> 09:24.060
BILL: You're a fool not to kill him.
ERIC: Killing him won't solve anything.

09:24.230 --> 09:28.314
-No, but it would keep him from killing us.
-Oh, he won't be doing any more killing.

09:28.485 --> 09:31.648
Eric, who the fuck are you right now?
He killed your family.

09:31.821 --> 09:33.322
Rip off his fucking head.

09:33.490 --> 09:34.980
Do not listen to them.

09:35.158 --> 09:37.865
I shall reward you handsomely.

09:38.078 --> 09:40.490
[RUSSELL GRUNTS]

09:46.669 --> 09:49.331
Well, that's humiliating. I'll take that.

09:50.507 --> 09:52.748
Sookie, come and hold
these chains together.

09:53.218 --> 09:54.378
As tight as you can.

09:56.888 --> 09:58.674
Don't even think about it, bitch.

09:58.848 --> 10:00.713
Are you kidding me?

10:00.892 --> 10:04.180
It's all I'll think about ever again.

10:04.354 --> 10:07.016
We should go to ground.
You stay here and watch him.

10:07.190 --> 10:09.272
I'm not babysitting this psycho
while you nap.

10:09.442 --> 10:11.182
ERIC:
He can't glamour you.

10:11.361 --> 10:14.319
Ginger's coming in later.
He would glamour her in a heartbeat.

10:14.489 --> 10:17.276
Pam, make one of the guest coffins
available for Mr. Compton.

10:17.450 --> 10:19.736
-I'm staying out here with Sookie.
ERIC: Suit yourself.

10:19.911 --> 10:22.527
-You have the bleeds.
-I won't leave you alone with him.

10:22.705 --> 10:26.072
I don't want to look at your face,
or any of your faces, for that matter.

10:26.251 --> 10:29.288
Go crawl back into your holes,
you creepy, cold freaks.

10:29.462 --> 10:31.043
It's Eric Northman.

10:31.214 --> 10:32.329
Please, be careful.

10:33.049 --> 10:35.711
I'm gonna need your van
and your help tonight.

10:37.095 --> 10:39.211
Do not stake him.

10:39.389 --> 10:41.471
How big a blood-demic y'all got going on?

10:41.641 --> 10:43.427
AN DY:
I wouldn't say it's an epidemic.

10:43.601 --> 10:46.263
Well, this here's blood enough
for about a hundred doses.

10:46.437 --> 10:49.099
That's a lot of hard-ons,
enhanced athletic performance...

10:49.274 --> 10:54.189
...and spontaneous healing of physical
infirmities for a town of how many?

10:54.779 --> 10:55.939
Twenty-seven hundred...

10:57.824 --> 11:00.236
...and 12. Excuse me, Sir.

11:01.077 --> 11:03.068
Stackhouse, why are you here?

11:03.246 --> 11:06.579
JASON: Are these the DEA guys?
-Who's this exactly?

11:07.083 --> 11:09.074
I'm Stackhouse.

11:09.252 --> 11:11.914
-I'm a deputy.
-Off-duty deputy. On leave, actually.

11:12.088 --> 11:15.171
Listen, I know all about the blood ring
in Hotshot.

11:15.341 --> 11:17.081
I'm the one who cracked it.

11:18.011 --> 11:20.468
-When y'all going in?
-My office.

11:21.639 --> 11:23.220
Get your--

11:26.436 --> 11:28.848
You ain't thinking about
tipping them off, are you?

11:29.022 --> 11:33.516
-I know your new girl's from there.
-All kinds of innocent people up there. Kids.

11:33.693 --> 11:35.149
So we just let them sell drugs?

11:35.320 --> 11:38.608
Well, if we stop them, somebody else
is just gonna start up. Right?

11:38.781 --> 11:41.773
You just rationalized away all need
for law enforcement.

11:42.243 --> 11:44.074
I don't know what that means exactly...

11:44.245 --> 11:48.113
...but you gotta stop
those government people out there. Please.

11:48.750 --> 11:50.115
Give me one good reason why.

11:51.711 --> 11:55.124
I would, but I swore
I wouldn't tell nobody.

11:55.632 --> 11:59.295
Jason, the fucking DEA is here
and they are going in today.

12:01.387 --> 12:03.548
-Fuck.
-You listen to me.

12:03.723 --> 12:07.136
You go warn Hotshot, you can kiss ever
becoming a cop goodbye.

12:24.535 --> 12:25.570
[SCREAMING]

12:29.999 --> 12:31.739
TARA:
No.

12:33.336 --> 12:35.497
No, please.

12:35.672 --> 12:37.628
[TARA SOBBING IN VOICE-OVER]

12:37.799 --> 12:39.960
Please.

12:43.763 --> 12:45.674
[MEN CHATTERING]

12:45.848 --> 12:47.588
What the heck?

12:57.277 --> 13:00.519
Oh, sweet Lord. She bit him.

13:00.905 --> 13:03.282
-Mom, what are y'all doing here?
MAXINE: Hoyt.

13:04.701 --> 13:08.694
You remember Mr. Rakestraw,
guidance counselor over to the high school.

13:09.539 --> 13:12.781
It sure is good to see you again, Hoyt.

13:13.209 --> 13:15.325
-Want to take a seat?
-I got work to do.

13:15.503 --> 13:17.243
I'm supervisor when Jason's not here.

13:17.422 --> 13:21.631
Yeah, well, I'm here for these folks
who really love you.

13:21.801 --> 13:25.259
They just want you to hear them out.
Then you can say what you want to say.

13:25.430 --> 13:27.421
Then we're done. Not a big deal.

13:28.474 --> 13:31.887
-Heh. Uh....
-Sit down, Hoyt.

13:32.353 --> 13:34.514
[CHAIN SAWS BUZZING]

13:37.233 --> 13:38.313
I'll start.

13:40.111 --> 13:41.567
"Dear Hoyt.

13:41.738 --> 13:44.650
I have known you ever Since
you were a safety patrol...

13:44.824 --> 13:47.281
...and helped me across the street
every day.

13:47.452 --> 13:50.535
You always smiled and said 'hey' to me.

13:50.705 --> 13:56.450
I have watched that kind, caring boy grow
into a fine, outstanding, great man.

13:56.627 --> 13:58.583
But now, instead of choosing life...

13:58.755 --> 14:02.339
...you want to go back to a vampire
who just wants to drink your blood...

14:02.508 --> 14:05.420
...and itjust breaks my heart."

14:05.595 --> 14:07.085
[SOBBING]

14:07.263 --> 14:08.469
Oh, well, now.

14:10.975 --> 14:13.933
RAKESTRAW:
Here. Mrs. Fortenberry.

14:21.069 --> 14:22.434
"Dear Hoyt.

14:22.779 --> 14:25.441
You are my first- and only-born.

14:25.615 --> 14:27.571
And if you think I am going to sit back...

14:27.742 --> 14:31.985
...and watch you throw your life away
on a redheaded dead girl...

14:32.163 --> 14:34.620
...you are sorely mistaken.

14:34.791 --> 14:36.782
There will be consequences."

14:37.085 --> 14:38.200
Yeah? Like what?

14:38.378 --> 14:41.870
-Like I will not let you back in my house.
-I already left.

14:42.048 --> 14:45.006
-I will disinherit you.
-You don't have any money anyway.

14:45.176 --> 14:48.293
-I am your mother.
-You're a mean, prejudiced old control freak.

14:48.471 --> 14:49.506
Okay, let's just try--

14:49.680 --> 14:52.296
You just shut up.
You're not even a real therapist.

14:52.475 --> 14:56.013
Everybody knows you got a bottle of
Malibu Rum in your desk, so shut up.

14:56.187 --> 14:58.644
Now, look. I love Jessica.

14:59.065 --> 15:00.145
I'm not leaving her.

15:00.316 --> 15:02.898
If you don't like it,
you can't be a part of my life.

15:03.069 --> 15:05.310
She is a killer. They're all killers.

15:05.488 --> 15:07.069
We saw that on the TV.

15:07.240 --> 15:08.821
Summer.

15:09.992 --> 15:11.152
I wish you well.

15:11.327 --> 15:13.943
I wish you the best husband
in the whole world.

15:14.330 --> 15:15.490
But that ain't me.

15:19.210 --> 15:22.452
[SOBBING]

15:26.050 --> 15:27.836
RAKESTRAW:
It's okay.

15:32.014 --> 15:33.675
You're early.

15:34.684 --> 15:37.767
I figured I'd make a couple of pots
of oyster stew this morning...

15:37.937 --> 15:41.521
...but I goddamn ran out the house
so fast, I forgot my key.

15:44.235 --> 15:45.816
No problem.

15:45.987 --> 15:47.898
Thank you.

15:52.702 --> 15:56.286
MAN:
Cross me and you're a dead man.

15:58.624 --> 15:59.659
Rough night?

16:01.669 --> 16:03.785
You could say that.

16:05.131 --> 16:09.249
Miss Stackhouse.

16:10.094 --> 16:13.211
I'd like to propose a deal.

16:13.973 --> 16:15.588
Oh.

16:16.392 --> 16:17.677
This ought to be good.

16:17.852 --> 16:22.562
I will give you my word that
I will not harm you or anyone you love.

16:22.732 --> 16:26.566
Stepping around the fact that your word's
worth about as much as tits on a turtle...

16:26.736 --> 16:27.771
...what else?

16:27.945 --> 16:29.981
One million dollars.

16:30.406 --> 16:31.486
-Five.
-Two.

16:31.657 --> 16:33.067
-Seven.
-Okay, 5.

16:33.242 --> 16:34.322
What else?

16:34.494 --> 16:38.157
I will kill Eric Northman.

16:39.582 --> 16:41.789
And Bill Compton.

16:42.835 --> 16:44.416
Both.

16:46.130 --> 16:47.745
Or neither.

16:48.633 --> 16:51.420
Or just one of your choosing.

16:52.136 --> 16:53.967
Both.

16:54.138 --> 16:57.926
And your house in Mississippi.
I like that house.

16:58.100 --> 17:01.183
-Done.
-What do I have to do in return?

17:02.980 --> 17:05.767
-Release me.
-No.

17:06.192 --> 17:09.434
It may not be me, but someday
some vampire is gonna rip you open...

17:09.612 --> 17:12.228
...to get at the essence inside of you.

17:12.406 --> 17:15.614
-There is no way around that.
-Shut up.

17:15.785 --> 17:19.619
You don't know what it is
to drink your blood.

17:19.789 --> 17:22.622
It is paradise.

17:22.792 --> 17:25.955
Arcadia. Nirvana.

17:26.128 --> 17:29.495
Who even knows what your blood
is capable of?

17:30.591 --> 17:34.334
I am surprised that your Mr. Compton
has showed such restraint.

17:34.512 --> 17:40.132
He is either a true gentleman
or very, very smart.

17:40.810 --> 17:41.799
Smart, why?

17:43.479 --> 17:45.390
By showing such a degree of control...

17:45.565 --> 17:49.103
...he's able to make the experience
last that much longer.

17:49.277 --> 17:51.689
That's basic tantra.

17:51.862 --> 17:54.114
But others won't be able
to stop themselves.

17:54.282 --> 17:58.321
They'll drain you dry,
which is a shame, really.

17:58.494 --> 18:04.660
But the rose only blooms
for a short while...

18:04.834 --> 18:06.790
.ulsuppose.

18:07.461 --> 18:09.372
[RUSSELL YELLING]

18:09.547 --> 18:11.663
That's enough out of you.

18:14.343 --> 18:16.595
You better hope to God I die...

18:16.762 --> 18:20.380
...because I would rip you open
and feed your entrails to you.

18:22.059 --> 18:24.345
Why are you carrying this around?

18:25.938 --> 18:27.519
He was the love of my life.

18:27.690 --> 18:30.602
-This isn't him.
-It will be.

18:32.278 --> 18:34.189
You think you can bring him back to life?

18:35.990 --> 18:38.697
-Of course not.
-Yes, you do.

18:39.201 --> 18:41.283
Somehow, involving my blood.

18:44.498 --> 18:47.035
-Fuck you.
-No.

18:47.752 --> 18:50.539
[RUSSELL SHOUTING IN GERMAN]

18:56.886 --> 18:59.298
[YELLING]

19:01.682 --> 19:03.798
[GARBAGE DISPOSAL WHIRRING]

19:06.187 --> 19:08.303
[LAUGHING]

19:14.111 --> 19:15.942
JASON:
Maybe everybody already took off.

19:16.113 --> 19:18.069
CRYSTAL:
No, they're here.

19:21.911 --> 19:23.447
Y'all come on out.

19:24.955 --> 19:27.082
It's me, Crystal.

19:27.249 --> 19:30.161
JASON: I don't think there's anybody here.
CRYSTAL: Shh.

19:32.254 --> 19:35.337
You brought him here?
Ain't enough you polluted your family?

19:35.508 --> 19:36.918
Now you bring outsiders?

19:37.176 --> 19:40.213
-I want both of y'all off my land.
-There ain't no time for this.

19:40.388 --> 19:43.471
-The DEA is coming for you.
JASON: And there's lots of them.

19:43.641 --> 19:46.804
Get rid of all the V or they're gonna
haul all of y'all off to jail.

19:46.977 --> 19:49.764
We never should have agreed to sell that.
Fucking fangers.

19:49.939 --> 19:53.102
Creek, you and Eddie Boy get that cooler.
Destroy that shit.

19:53.275 --> 19:55.266
CALVIN: Yeah, and bring me some guns.
Gasoline too.

19:55.444 --> 19:56.604
Yes, sir, Daddy.

19:56.779 --> 19:58.940
This don't make a difference
between me and you.

19:59.115 --> 20:02.653
Well, don't you think it should?
I'm trying to help your family out here.

20:02.827 --> 20:04.988
Well, we don't need
none of your fucking help.

20:05.162 --> 20:07.278
We were doing fine on our own
for a long time.

20:07.998 --> 20:09.704
IS that so?

20:10.126 --> 20:14.620
Because I see a lot of people
who look dirty and hungry...

20:14.797 --> 20:17.209
...and kids who probably ain't
in school...

20:17.383 --> 20:19.795
...and several people obviously
got dental problems.

20:19.969 --> 20:22.130
Here you go, Uncle Daddy Calvin.

20:22.722 --> 20:25.134
Bufort, I want you to get all the meth
and the gear.

20:25.307 --> 20:29.050
Put it in the back of the tow truck.
Eddie Boy, you park it deep in the woods.

20:29.228 --> 20:31.059
I'm throwing this vamper shit
in the latrine.

20:31.230 --> 20:32.390
[GUNSHOT]

