-She can either get in that truck herself...

24:28.926 --> 24:31.542
...or I can shoot you and put her in it.
Her choice.

24:36.725 --> 24:37.760
I have to.

24:37.935 --> 24:39.926
-No, don't.
FELTON: Ten.

24:40.604 --> 24:43.721
Listen, when he shoots me, you change
and run and don't look back.

24:43.899 --> 24:47.266
-Nine.
-This is what I was born for, Jason.

24:47.444 --> 24:50.231
-This is what's in store for me.
-You know that's not true.

24:50.406 --> 24:53.239
Who'll keep me from shooting him
and dragging you off anyway?

24:53.409 --> 24:56.993
Because I know you ain't all bad.

24:57.162 --> 25:00.370
I know you wouldn't do that
to these women and kids.

25:00.541 --> 25:02.406
You know, with you and Daddy
both gone...

25:03.252 --> 25:06.585
...well, somebody gotta take care
of everybody that's left.

25:07.089 --> 25:11.298
And that somebody is you.

25:26.984 --> 25:28.895
Tell me how to.

25:29.069 --> 25:31.811
You just help them, however you can.

25:32.823 --> 25:35.940
If this is the last time I ever see you....

25:37.161 --> 25:40.824
I will find you. I promise.

25:42.332 --> 25:43.788
I'm so sorry, Jason.

25:46.754 --> 25:50.121
Don't you worry about your people.
You just stay safe.

25:50.591 --> 25:52.047
I love you.

25:55.054 --> 25:56.089
She worth it?

26:14.823 --> 26:16.484
Okay.

26:20.162 --> 26:21.993
Everybody...

26:25.876 --> 26:28.162
...my name is Jason.

26:35.344 --> 26:37.551
-Mama.
-Baby?

26:37.721 --> 26:40.007
Tara Mae? Baby?

26:40.182 --> 26:42.298
Don't come in here.

26:47.356 --> 26:49.221
Reverend Daniels?

26:49.608 --> 26:51.109
Hello.

26:52.194 --> 26:55.357
I spilled some lemonade on my pants.

26:56.365 --> 26:58.481
LETTIE MAE:
Baby, it ain't what it look like.

26:58.659 --> 27:03.073
Yeah. Your mother was just helping me with
my sermon when I spilled the lemonade.

27:03.247 --> 27:04.737
LETTIE MAE:
Tara Mae.

27:04.915 --> 27:06.576
I know this is embarrassing, but--

27:06.750 --> 27:09.412
Does his wife know? His kids?

27:12.214 --> 27:13.920
He gonna tell them.

27:14.091 --> 27:16.207
-Soon.
-Soon.

27:17.553 --> 27:18.884
He loves me.

27:19.972 --> 27:23.055
He gonna leave his wife.
He just needs time.

27:24.143 --> 27:26.179
I'm in love.

27:26.353 --> 27:27.718
Be happy for me.

27:28.355 --> 27:33.725
God knows I don't have any business
judging anybody, but aren't you Sick of this?

27:33.902 --> 27:36.393
Don't you want to change your life
while you got time?

27:36.572 --> 27:37.607
I am changing.

27:39.575 --> 27:43.113
I'm gonna be a minister's wife.

27:45.330 --> 27:48.288
I'm gonna be happy at last.

27:59.845 --> 28:01.836
Good luck, Mama.

28:10.522 --> 28:12.262
I really hope you will be.

28:47.017 --> 28:48.348
Tommy!

28:50.145 --> 28:54.013
ARLENE: I don't know ifl can put up
with Sam being an asshole again today.

28:54.191 --> 28:58.150
Not after everything I've been through
in the last 24 hours.

28:59.112 --> 29:02.696
I'm inside her right now.

29:03.533 --> 29:05.034
She can't get rid of me.

29:06.328 --> 29:09.491
WOMAN [IN VOICE-OVER]:
This is hell. We 're in hell.

29:09.665 --> 29:11.530
[BOTH YELLING]

29:15.254 --> 29:16.539
Are you crazy?

29:17.881 --> 29:20.167
-You should not be working.
-We need the money.

29:20.342 --> 29:21.752
Do you wanna lose this baby?

29:22.261 --> 29:24.252
Of course not.

29:35.023 --> 29:37.605
I am seeing things.

29:37.776 --> 29:39.016
Bad things.

29:39.194 --> 29:41.401
-What kind of things?
-Blood.

29:42.656 --> 29:44.442
Ghosts.

29:44.616 --> 29:46.607
I saw a monster head on you.

29:46.785 --> 29:49.242
-Look, where are you right now?
-Merlotte 's.

29:53.750 --> 29:55.490
Am I schizophrenic like my mama?

29:55.877 --> 29:58.710
Look, I'm gonna be there
as soon as I can, okay?

29:58.880 --> 30:00.381
I'm leaving right now.

30:00.549 --> 30:06.215
Okay. Okay. Hurry up, please.
Hurry up.

30:22.070 --> 30:23.571
Hear that?

30:25.449 --> 30:29.237
That's my wolves coming to rescue me.

30:29.745 --> 30:31.531
Are you sure you're not hungry?

30:31.705 --> 30:35.072
I could make you
a peanut butter and butter sandwich. No?

30:35.834 --> 30:37.870
[SCREAMS]

30:40.130 --> 30:42.291
Could you please not do that?

30:42.632 --> 30:45.874
-How did you know to come for me?
ALCIDE: Here because Eric called me.

30:46.053 --> 30:48.214
Said he needed my help with something.

30:48.388 --> 30:50.128
Promised to settle all my dad's debts.

30:51.266 --> 30:52.972
Oh.

30:53.143 --> 30:55.634
Why? You in trouble again?

30:56.146 --> 30:57.761
When am I not in trouble?

31:01.610 --> 31:02.770
IS Janice okay?

31:02.944 --> 31:05.435
My whole family's okay, knock on wood.

31:05.614 --> 31:07.730
Debbie's gone missing, though.

31:11.620 --> 31:14.703
I've been thinking about you. A lot.

31:15.791 --> 31:17.702
That's nice, I guess.

31:19.086 --> 31:21.793
-I even had a couple dreams about you.
-Alcide.

31:21.963 --> 31:23.373
No.

31:23.548 --> 31:26.381
I'm just saying,
it sure is good to see you again.

31:27.969 --> 31:30.221
I'd have hated
if we never saw each other again.

31:30.389 --> 31:32.254
Don't, okay?

31:32.891 --> 31:34.631
Don't be such a good guy right now.

31:34.810 --> 31:36.766
I can't help it if I'm a good guy.

31:36.937 --> 31:38.393
[LAUGHS]

31:38.563 --> 31:42.476
Yet every full moon, he turns into a wolf
and kills and eats his prey.

31:42.651 --> 31:44.562
Rabbits and squirrels, not people.

31:44.736 --> 31:45.851
Details.

31:47.823 --> 31:49.188
Good, you're here.

31:49.366 --> 31:52.278
-Your truck out front?
ALCIDE: Yup.

32:03.672 --> 32:06.163
Let's go. Got a lot to do.

32:07.134 --> 32:08.965
Sookie, stay here.

32:09.136 --> 32:10.251
Pam'll protect you.

32:10.429 --> 32:15.298
Feel safer protecting myself, Since I now
know I'm basically vampire crack.

32:17.853 --> 32:22.187
By the way, I rescind the invitation
to my house for all vampires present.

32:22.357 --> 32:24.348
So don't even think about
following me home.

32:26.528 --> 32:30.191
ERIC: Get up.
RUSSELL: I do not take orders from anybody.

32:30.365 --> 32:31.696
ERIC:
Suit yourself.

32:31.867 --> 32:33.607
[GROANING]

32:33.785 --> 32:36.902
ERIC: If you two have finished
eye-fucking each other, can we go?

32:37.080 --> 32:40.948
Eric, do not bring that thing
back inside this bar.

32:57.559 --> 32:58.548
[DOOR BANGS]

32:58.727 --> 33:00.433
MAN:
That's all we need.

33:03.231 --> 33:06.018
Your so-called deputy here
tipped the suspects off.

33:06.193 --> 33:07.933
Whole place was cleaned out.

33:08.111 --> 33:10.022
Nobody there except him
and two dead guys.

33:10.197 --> 33:13.940
I told you, they was killed by Felton Norris,
who then stole my truck...

33:14.117 --> 33:17.905
...Louisiana license plate Larry-Charlie...

33:18.872 --> 33:20.783
...WiIIie-8â€”M-2.

33:20.957 --> 33:22.788
He took the V and his gun with him.

33:22.959 --> 33:27.498
Now I gotta call fucking New Orleans,
tell them what a clusterfuck you got here.

33:27.672 --> 33:29.833
Sons of bitches, backwater hicks.

33:30.008 --> 33:33.500
Where's my Luckies?
Somebody bring me my Luckies.

33:33.678 --> 33:35.418
Nice.

33:35.597 --> 33:40.182
Way you just fucked yourself and me both,
that's pretty impressive.

33:40.352 --> 33:43.560
And thanks for spilling the beans
about Eggs to Tara.

33:43.730 --> 33:47.939
Andy, this ain't about us.

33:48.109 --> 33:49.269
There are bigger things.

33:49.444 --> 33:51.776
Like what? A girl?

33:51.947 --> 33:56.907
Like a whole lot of other people
who ain't really able to fend for themselves.

33:58.203 --> 34:00.945
Well, I hope you realize
you just screwed your one chance...

34:01.122 --> 34:03.374
...of ever making something of yourself.

34:04.834 --> 34:08.042
Sometimes the right thing to do
is the wrong thing.

34:10.131 --> 34:12.292
And I know I did the right thing.

34:23.520 --> 34:24.976
Come here, come here.

34:25.146 --> 34:27.762
It's okay, it's okay, it's okay.

34:31.987 --> 34:33.818
What the fuck is happening to me,
Jesus?

34:33.989 --> 34:38.028
My first memory is of my mama talking
to motherfuckers who wasn't there.

34:38.201 --> 34:40.613
IS that what's happening to me?

34:40.787 --> 34:42.618
I don't think so. I really don't.

34:42.789 --> 34:47.533
You just opened up something inside you.
You're much more sensitive now.

34:47.711 --> 34:51.795
I don't want to be sensitive to that shit.
I want it as far away from me as it can be.

34:51.965 --> 34:53.830
Listen to me, Lafayette. Look.

34:54.301 --> 34:56.508
When my Tio Luca
started teaching me magic...

34:56.678 --> 34:58.839
...I was in a sweat lodge for three days...

34:59.014 --> 35:02.347
...and the earth started talking to me,
literally, with multiple faces.

35:02.517 --> 35:04.098
This don't make me feel better.

35:04.269 --> 35:06.931
After, I started seeing things
that people wanted to hide.

35:07.272 --> 35:08.682
But it wore off.

35:09.649 --> 35:11.560
Or I just got used to it, I don't know.

35:12.319 --> 35:14.025
Now, wait a minute.

35:14.404 --> 35:16.190
You said somebody taught you magic?

35:17.699 --> 35:18.688
Yeah.

35:20.410 --> 35:22.446
You kind of need to be taught.

35:23.872 --> 35:25.578
What are you? Huh?

35:25.999 --> 35:27.364
I'm a brujo.

35:30.378 --> 35:32.460
-A witch.
-You're a witch.

35:33.298 --> 35:36.631
You're a witch who's a nurse
who's a dude.

35:40.889 --> 35:43.972
Oh, well, shit,
I guess I lucked out, then, huh?

36:36.611 --> 36:39.102
Oh, my God.

36:40.156 --> 36:41.441
I love it.

36:41.616 --> 36:42.776
Really?

36:42.951 --> 36:44.737
I just needed to make a change.

36:44.911 --> 36:46.026
Change is good.

36:52.711 --> 36:54.827
Feels like forever since we just hung out.

36:55.004 --> 36:57.165
It has been forever.

36:58.466 --> 36:59.876
I've been such a bitch to you.

37:00.051 --> 37:03.919
Hey, don't beat yourself up,
not after everything you've been through.

37:04.097 --> 37:05.803
I hate being mad at you.

37:05.974 --> 37:08.807
I know. You're basically my sister.

37:09.853 --> 37:11.468
We shouldn't be mad at each other.

37:13.982 --> 37:16.974
-What the hell happened in your bedroom?
-You don't wanna know.

37:17.152 --> 37:19.143
-Vampire?
-Werewolf.

37:22.657 --> 37:24.818
I'm gonna run over to Merlotte's
for a while.

37:26.411 --> 37:27.821
I need to see Lafayette.

37:27.996 --> 37:29.782
Will I see you later?

37:29.956 --> 37:32.368
Yeah. I won't be gone long.

37:32.542 --> 37:35.500
Good, because I don't
wanna be alone right now.

37:44.721 --> 37:46.052
Bye.

37:56.900 --> 37:58.515
ALCIDE:
We're done now, right?

37:58.693 --> 38:02.356
My dad's out of debt.
You leave him and my family alone.

38:09.496 --> 38:11.953
[SCREAMING]

38:13.458 --> 38:15.323
RUSSELL:
Just kill me, Viking.

38:15.502 --> 38:17.538
Take your fucking revenge.

38:17.712 --> 38:19.919
ERIC:
That was the original plan.

38:20.507 --> 38:22.043
Then I was thinking...

38:22.217 --> 38:25.425
...how do I know
beyond the shadow of a doubt...

38:25.595 --> 38:28.211
...that you won't find some sort of
peace aftenNards?

38:29.224 --> 38:31.340
Heaven. Oh, dear.

38:31.518 --> 38:33.554
GODRIC [IN SWEDISH]:
Everyone deserves peace, Eric.

38:35.897 --> 38:38.559
I can't bear the thought of you
finding any redemption.

38:38.733 --> 38:42.567
Wrapped in Silver, encased in concrete.

38:42.737 --> 38:45.399
You won't be going anywhere
for at least a hundred years.

38:45.573 --> 38:48.736
A hundred years, that's nothing to me.

38:48.910 --> 38:50.525
That's a nap.

38:50.703 --> 38:53.115
That's 100 years with no escape
from your grief...

38:54.582 --> 38:57.574
...no escape from knowing
I took what you love most...

38:58.044 --> 38:59.875
...and you will never get it back.

39:00.046 --> 39:02.913
A hundred years during which
you will go mad...

39:03.091 --> 39:05.423
...madder even than you are now.

39:05.593 --> 39:07.879
And you are as mad as a fucking hatter.

39:08.054 --> 39:12.388
A hundred years for me to plan exactly
how I'm gonna kill you both!

39:13.935 --> 39:15.391
Have fun.

39:15.728 --> 39:17.855
You make me bleed, my child.

39:19.691 --> 39:21.181
So much hatred.

39:21.359 --> 39:23.395
This is who I am, Godric.

39:23.570 --> 39:26.733
This is what you made!

39:27.198 --> 39:30.565
Do you not see that he is the one
who is mad?

39:31.119 --> 39:32.609
Speaking to phantoms?

39:32.787 --> 39:35.324
All I can see is how utterly
powerless you are...

39:35.498 --> 39:37.955
...knowing that you're about
to be buried alive.

39:38.126 --> 39:41.243
And honestly, it's a thing of great beauty.

39:44.674 --> 39:47.006
[CHUCKUNG]

39:47.969 --> 39:50.961
You will regret this.

39:51.472 --> 39:52.973
Maybe.

39:53.182 --> 39:54.922
But right now, it feels fucking good.

39:56.227 --> 39:58.343
[YELLING]

40:35.516 --> 40:40.977
When fate presents one with such
a grand opportunity, what else is one to do?

40:45.610 --> 40:47.896
[GRUNTING]

40:50.156 --> 40:52.317
[GROANING]

40:52.492 --> 40:53.698
[LINE DIALING]

40:55.036 --> 40:56.446
[LINE RINGING]

40:56.621 --> 40:59.078
MAN: This is Ruben.
-[|N ERIC'S VOICE] It's Northman.

40:59.248 --> 41:02.706
I want you to find my progeny, Pam,
and kill her. Now.

41:14.722 --> 41:15.973
HOYT:
No peeking.

41:16.140 --> 41:18.256
And no using special vampire powers,
either.

41:18.434 --> 41:20.049
JESSICA:
Okay.

41:20.770 --> 41:23.512
HOYT:
Easy, easy. I gotcha.

41:23.898 --> 41:25.434
All right.

41:28.903 --> 41:30.439
A little dip.

41:31.406 --> 41:32.441
There we go.

41:37.245 --> 41:38.530
Would you please come in?

41:38.705 --> 41:40.241
[JESSICA LAUGHING]

41:41.958 --> 41:43.414
It smells funny.

41:50.216 --> 41:51.752
Hoyt.

41:51.968 --> 41:55.085
-Hope you like it. I already paid the deposit.
-It's totally cute.

41:55.263 --> 41:57.925
